[[div class="peppo-head"]]
Special Containment Procedures
[[/div]]

------

No new [[[taboo|names]]] or designations are to be used in reference to [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]]. All names and designations currently and previously applied to [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] are considered lost. 

Physical barriers are ineffective against [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]], as are traditional firearms and other ballistic weaponry. [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] is not susceptible to damage by heat, but displays an emotional aversion to fire and may be corralled via the use of flamethrowers until its manifestation ends. Once an [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] manifestation is confirmed, the area is to be immediately evacuated. Standard misinformation protocols are in place to account for loss of life and property damage caused by [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]].

The current whereabouts of [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] and whether it will continue to manifest are currently unknown. A provisional containment chamber, designed to produce consistent flame along the surface of its walls and ceiling, has been constructed at Site-19 to house [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] should it ever be successfully captured. A measure to neutralize [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] via the deliberate extinction of //Betula pubescens// has been considered and rejected by the O2 Congress.

[[div class="peppo-head"]]
Description
[[/div]]

------

[!-- [[div class="peppo-head2"]]
Appearance 
[[/div]] --]


**[[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]]** is an abstract logomorphic entity which interfaces with baseline reality via avatars composed from scraps of birch[[footnote]]Specifically //Betula pubescens//, commonly referred to as the white birch.[[/footnote]] bark arranged into a humanoid shape. These avatars consistently possess heads resembling the skull of a male deer, sans lower jaw, with a dense cluster of branchlike antlers. Soft tissue organs resembling lidded eyes constantly shift across the surface of these antlers, moving in no discernible pattern.

Vessels under [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]]'s control take on an extraphysical and/or demiconceptual level of solidity that necessarily supersedes the environment around it; consequently, when a part of [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]]'s body applies any amount of physical pressure against an object of baseline-reality solidity, the object's mass will warp, collapse, or otherwise be displaced as necessary to accommodate [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]]'s movement.[[footnote]] An important exception to this property is the gravitational force of [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]]'s own weight against the ground it rests on. If this exception did not exist, [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] would theoretically fall through the Earth itself until it reached the planet's gravitational center.[[/footnote]] 

Matter displaced by interaction with [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] will behave in a manner similar to semi-solids or high-viscosity fluids, irrespective of the affected substance's actual density or material composition, and without causing any actual change to its state of matter. Displacement of mass is not reversed after contact with [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] has ceased, nor is any damage that the object would naturally incur from an abrupt alteration of its structure. 

[[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] manifests once every five years by converting mass from a //Betula pubescens// tree into a new bodily vessel.[[footnote]]It is unknown if [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] purposefully selects which tree it manifests from, or if the selection is random or otherwise outside [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]]'s control.[[/footnote]] Once formed, [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] will seek out populated areas and attempt to destroy any person or structure it encounters through the displacement of matter. This assault will continue until the sun has fully set, at which time [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]]'s vessel will break down into non-anomalous tree bark. Local flora will often grow at a greatly accelerated rate in the vicinity of [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]]; this effect appears to be incidental rather than deliberate.  

[[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] bears an ancillary nomenclative abnormality which causes a gradual physio-conceptual degradation of any name or designation applied to it, culminating in the name or designation being completely and irretrievably removed from all physical and conceptual planes. Names and designations lost to [[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] will disappear from written records and recordings, and may lead to aberrant behavior of the medium through which the name or designation was expressed, including (but not limited to) data files, printed documents, and speech organs/orifices. 

[[span id="inviz"]]SCP-8400[[/span]] has ignored all attempts at communication from civilians and Foundation personnel, with the sole exception Dr. Delaney Martlet.

[[div class="peppo-head"]]
Encounters with Dr. Martlet
[[/div]]

------
@@@@
@@@@


